addBeneficiary(address).details: Allow community managers to add beneficiaries.

addManager(address).details: Allow community managers to add other managers.

edit(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint256,uin.details: Allow community managers to edit community variables.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

initialize(address,uint256,uint256,uint2.details: Constructor with custom fields, choosen by the community.

params.claimAmount_: Base amount to be claim by the benificiary.
params.firstManager_: Comminuty's first manager. Will be able to add others.
params.incrementInterval_: Increment interval used in each claim.
params.maxClaim_: Limit that a beneficiary can claim at once.
params.previousCommunity_: previous smart contract address of community.

lockBeneficiary(address).details: Allow community managers to lock beneficiaries.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

removeBeneficiary(address).details: Allow community managers to remove beneficiaries.

removeManager(address).details: Allow community managers to remove other managers.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unlockBeneficiary(address).details: Allow community managers to unlock locked beneficiaries.

lock().notice: Allow community managers to lock community claims.

migrateFunds(address,address).notice: Migrate funds in current community to new one.

unlock().notice: Allow community managers to unlock community claims.

userdoc.notice: Welcome to the Community contract. For each community there will be one contract like this being deployed by CommunityAdmin contract. This enable us to save tokens on the contract itself, and avoid the problems of having everything in one single contract. Each community has it's own members and and managers.
